CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1952, pg. 33, reads: "Vice Presidential Candidate Greeted - The Republican bigwigs were out in full force at Syria Mosque when Vice Presidential nominee Richard Nixon visited Pittsburgh last week for a major address.  Here are Congressman Robert Corbett, Mrs. Patricia Nixon, Senator Edward Martin, Senator James Duff, the candidate, Governor John S. Fine and State Republican Chairman Harvey M. Taylor. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Senator Edward Martin, Senator James Duff, vice presidential candidate Richard Nixon, and Governor John S. Fine, standing on stage in Syria Mosque
